OL,3,CReynolds gives instructions to British
OL,4,CSteel after MPs back emergency law
OL,6,FEarlier on Saturday, MPs and peers had
OL,7,Fapproved emergency legislation without
OL,8,Fopposition, giving Mr Reynolds the
OL,9,Fpower to require British Steel to keep
OL,10,Fthe Scunthorpe plant going after talks
OL,11,Fwith its Chinese owner, Jingye, broke
OL,12,Fdown.
OL,14,FIn a highly unusual step, the
OL,15,FGovernment had recalled Parliament
OL,16,Ffrom its Easter recess at short
OL,17,Fnotice, fearing that the blast
OL,18,Ffurnaces could be irrevocably closed
OL,19,Fwithin days without urgent action.
