OL,3,CReynolds gives instructions to British
OL,4,CSteel after MPs back emergency law
OL,6,FSaturday's legislation stopped short
OL,7,Fof fully nationalising British Steel,
OL,8,Finstead allowing Mr Reynolds to
OL,9,Finstruct the company to maintain the
OL,10,Fblast furnaces, keep staff employed
OL,11,Fand continue to purchase the raw
OL,12,Fmaterials needed to make steel, with
OL,13,Fcriminal penalties for executives if
OL,14,Fthey refuse.
