OL,6,FBut the Conservatives said the
OL,7,FGovernment should have acted sooner,
OL,8,Fwith shadow leader of the House Alex
OL,9,FBurghart accusing ministers of making
OL,10,F"a total pig's breakfast of this whole
OL,11,Farrangement".
OL,13,FShadow business secretary Andrew
OL,14,FGriffith said the Government was
OL,15,Fseeking a "blank cheque", while Tory
OL,16,Fleader Kemi Badenoch claimed Labour
OL,17,Fhad "botched" a deal she had
OL,18,Fnegotiated with British Steel while
OL,19,Fbusiness secretary.
